We divide $p(x)$ by $q(x)$ and find the remainder:
\[
\begin{array}{c|cccccccccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{1} & x^{11} & x^{10} & x^9 & x^8 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\cline{2-13}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{1} & x^{11} & x^{10} & x^9 & x^8 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -1 & -x^{10} & -x^9 & -x^8 & -x^7 & -x^6 & -x^5 & -x^4 & -x^3 & -x^2 & -x & 1 \\
\cline{2-13}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & x^{10} & x^9 & x^8 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0 & x^9 & x^8 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\cline{4-13}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0 & 0 & x^8 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & x^7 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\cline{6-13}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & x^6 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & x^5 & x^4 & x^3 & x^2 & x & 1 \\
