1^{2004} & 2^{2004} & 3^{2004} & \cdots & 2005^{2004}
\end{vmatrix}
= \begin{vmatrix}
1 & 2 & 3 & \cdots & 2005 \\
0 & 4 & 9 & \cdots & 4010025 \\
0 & 0 & 27 & \cdots & 729000075 \\
\vdots & \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 2005^{2004}
\end{vmatrix}.$$

By expanding the determinant along the first column, we get:

$$\begin{vmatrix}
1 & 2 & 3 & \cdots & 2005 \\
0 & 4 & 9 & \cdots & 4010025 \\
0 & 0 & 27 & \cdots & 729000075 \\
\vdots & \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
0 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 2005^{2004}
\end{vmatrix}
= 1 \cdot \begin{vmatrix}
4 & 9 & \cdots & 40

